WEBVTT

00:01.479 --> 00:04.003
[instrumental music]

00:44.174 --> 00:47.047
[music continues]

01:17.468 --> 01:20.123
[music continues]

01:24.171 --> 01:26.173
[gasps]
Help! Help!

01:26.216 --> 01:27.391
Help..

01:50.284 --> 01:53.156
[music continues]

02:23.273 --> 02:26.146
[music continues]

02:27.495 --> 02:30.367
[indistinct chatter]

02:35.067 --> 02:38.201
Excuse me. Any chance
you're interested to tour?

02:38.245 --> 02:39.898
We're offering special on

02:39.942 --> 02:43.032
New England architectural
elements featuring..

02:43.075 --> 02:44.860
...cornices.

02:44.903 --> 02:47.645
No, thanks.
Cornices aren't my thing.

02:47.689 --> 02:48.907
Yeah, me neither.

02:54.174 --> 02:56.263
So..

02:56.306 --> 02:57.786
...your first time
on the island?

02:57.829 --> 02:59.135
Yeah.

02:59.179 --> 03:00.876
No.

03:00.919 --> 03:03.922
- I was actually born here.
- That's impossible!

03:03.966 --> 03:06.534
Been in summering in Selkie my
whole life. I'd remember you.

03:06.577 --> 03:08.057
Did you just turn summer
into a verb?

03:08.100 --> 03:09.928
I did.

03:09.972 --> 03:12.322
- I'm TJ.
- Miranda.

03:12.366 --> 03:13.628
You're Amelia's daughter.

03:15.673 --> 03:17.197
- You know Amelia?
- Well, yeah.

03:17.240 --> 03:19.590
I mean,
it's a pretty small island.

03:19.634 --> 03:21.853
'Everyone knows everyone.'

03:21.897 --> 03:23.290
I suppose you do sorta
look alike.

03:24.987 --> 03:26.554
I wouldn't know.

03:26.597 --> 03:29.644
I haven't seen her
since I was preverbal.

03:29.687 --> 03:34.431
My dad kind of died
and Amelia's my next of kin.

03:34.475 --> 03:36.128
- I'm sorry to hear that.
- Yeah, thanks.

03:37.391 --> 03:38.870
Well, brace yourself.

03:38.914 --> 03:40.611
The return of Amelia's
long lost daughter

03:40.655 --> 03:43.310
is gonna be the biggest news
around here since..

03:43.353 --> 03:45.703
...general store was robbed
like ten years ago.

03:45.747 --> 03:47.705
Any chance I'll be no news?

03:47.749 --> 03:50.621
- Probably not.
- Okay.

03:50.665 --> 03:52.710
[TJ]
'So how long are you in town?'

03:52.754 --> 03:54.277
I don't know.

03:54.321 --> 03:56.584
I don't even know
where I'm going to live.

03:56.627 --> 03:58.107
The address
my social worker gave me

03:58.150 --> 04:00.805
just said, "The Mariner."

04:00.849 --> 04:02.981
New Englanders still practice
the fine old tradition

04:03.025 --> 04:04.461
of naming our homes.

04:04.505 --> 04:06.289
I live in Beauport.

04:06.333 --> 04:07.682
You can tell it's fancy
'cause it's French.

04:09.597 --> 04:10.641
Wanna see your new pad?

04:11.990 --> 04:13.165
Wait, like right now?

04:13.209 --> 04:14.254
Yeah.

04:15.211 --> 04:16.430
Come on.

04:16.473 --> 04:18.214
[instrumental music]

04:18.257 --> 04:24.089
♪ I never loved
anyone like this ♪

04:24.133 --> 04:27.919
♪ It's so hard

04:27.963 --> 04:30.966
♪ To be still

04:32.315 --> 04:34.665
♪ Come around again

04:35.884 --> 04:41.542
♪ Lead me on your way

04:42.499 --> 04:44.632
♪ Back home

04:44.675 --> 04:46.329
Straight ahead.

04:46.373 --> 04:47.548
'The big green one's
The Mariner.'

04:48.462 --> 04:50.333
Home sweet home.

04:50.377 --> 04:52.117
[TJ]
'See that house down there?'

04:52.161 --> 04:56.165
'That's Beauport.
Door's always open.'

04:56.208 --> 04:58.167
I know the island looks raw,
but it's actually pretty sweet

04:58.210 --> 05:00.778
once you get used to
living in a digital desert.

05:00.822 --> 05:02.954
Please tell me that doesn't mean
what I think it means.

05:02.998 --> 05:05.348
No cell tower on the island.
Or internet.

05:05.392 --> 05:06.871
Except for
the coffee shop in town.

05:09.396 --> 05:11.572
Worried about that boyfriend
of yours back in..

05:11.615 --> 05:13.530
Portland. Nice try.

05:14.531 --> 05:18.100
♪ In years

05:18.143 --> 05:20.015
♪ You gave me what I want

05:20.058 --> 05:21.930
♪ You gave me what I want

05:21.973 --> 05:23.584
♪ You gave me what I want

05:23.627 --> 05:25.281
♪ You gave me what I want

05:25.325 --> 05:27.327
♪ I got nothin' left ♪

05:33.376 --> 05:36.205
[music continues]

05:48.130 --> 05:51.307
[Miranda]
For some reason I thought Maine
would be a little more rustic.

05:51.351 --> 05:52.830
Oh, this is nothin'.

05:52.874 --> 05:54.484
Wait till you see
some of the yachts at the club.

05:54.528 --> 05:56.094
Including yours?

05:56.138 --> 05:58.532
[Ginny]
'Hey, TJ!'

05:58.575 --> 06:02.579
- Friend?
- Girlfriend, actually. Kind of.

06:02.623 --> 06:05.234
- Right.
- Hey, hottie with a body.

06:05.277 --> 06:06.627
[chuckles]
Hi!

06:10.718 --> 06:12.546
God, I missed you!

06:14.330 --> 06:16.941
Oh, is this the Miller's new au pair.

06:16.985 --> 06:18.508
Do you speak English?

06:18.552 --> 06:20.858
Uh, Ginny,
this is Amelia's daughter.

06:20.902 --> 06:22.251
Oh!

06:22.294 --> 06:24.384
Oh, my God!
I am so embarrassed.

06:24.427 --> 06:27.343
I, I saw those cut-offs
and I just assumed..

06:27.387 --> 06:29.301
- Sorry.
- I'm Miranda.

06:29.345 --> 06:30.781
Ginny Cunningham.

06:30.825 --> 06:32.522
I would invite you to come
to the club with us

06:32.566 --> 06:35.743
but I'm sure you and Amelia
have a ton of catching up to do.

06:35.786 --> 06:37.788
- Yeah.
- Oh, there's Quire.

06:37.832 --> 06:39.747
- She has the party favors.
- 'Oh!'

06:39.790 --> 06:41.313
Bobby's already waiting for us.

06:41.357 --> 06:42.619
Yeah, well, uh,
I'll catch up with ya.

06:44.142 --> 06:45.274
Okay, well, hurry up.

06:47.015 --> 06:49.539
Well, guess I better
get this over with.

06:49.583 --> 06:50.671
[Amelia]
'Miranda!'

06:53.413 --> 06:55.153
Sure you don't want back-up?

06:55.197 --> 06:57.373
I don't mean to brag
but moms love me.

06:57.417 --> 06:58.809
Wish I could say the same.

07:00.942 --> 07:03.814
[instrumental music]

07:10.517 --> 07:11.953
Hi.

07:11.996 --> 07:12.997
Hey.

07:15.260 --> 07:16.740
How was the ride over?

07:17.741 --> 07:19.395
Fine.

07:19.439 --> 07:20.440
Boaty.

07:22.267 --> 07:24.487
Oh, you-you must be starving.

07:24.531 --> 07:25.532
Let's get you home.

07:27.011 --> 07:29.884
[instrumental music]

07:47.205 --> 07:48.859
This place is huge.

07:50.557 --> 07:52.733
What do you do? I..

07:52.776 --> 07:55.779
I tried Googling you
but I didn't find much.

07:55.823 --> 07:58.521
Greg never told you
anything about me?

07:58.565 --> 08:01.263
Didn't ask.

08:01.306 --> 08:03.787
Well, um, I got my degree
in art history.

08:03.831 --> 08:06.094
But, right now, I mostly write.

08:06.137 --> 08:08.357
Exhibition announcements,
art reviews..

08:08.400 --> 08:10.315
That kinda thing.

08:10.359 --> 08:12.187
Cool.

08:12.230 --> 08:14.145
What about you? Any hobbies?

08:14.189 --> 08:17.540
- 'Or do you play sports?'
- Uh, no.

08:17.584 --> 08:20.500
Hand-eye coordination
isn't really one of my skills.

08:20.543 --> 08:23.198
You get that from me.
I can't throw a ball five feet.

08:24.939 --> 08:26.288
My bag is kind of heavy.

08:26.331 --> 08:27.724
Can you show me
where I'm sleeping?

08:28.986 --> 08:30.379
Sure.

08:30.422 --> 08:31.554
'This way.'

08:37.604 --> 08:40.520
[indistinct music]

08:43.957 --> 08:45.916
Hey. Is your vision
getting worse?

08:45.960 --> 08:47.309
'Cause your crazy hot girlfriend
is over there

08:47.352 --> 08:49.354
'getting easier
by the second.'

08:49.398 --> 08:51.095
Not sure want to be
tied down this summer.

08:51.139 --> 08:53.707
Okay. Just let me know
when you're done with her.

08:53.750 --> 08:55.404
'Cause I'm totally down
for sloppy seconds.

08:55.926 --> 08:57.058
Classy!

08:59.756 --> 09:03.368
Alright! All aboard!
Oh.

09:04.631 --> 09:05.980
'Oh, cheers.'

09:06.023 --> 09:07.938
[chuckling]

09:09.505 --> 09:12.116
God, I love summer.

09:12.160 --> 09:13.901
Hey, I heard you met
Amelia's daughter on the ferry.

09:13.944 --> 09:15.206
- I did.
- 'Okay.'

09:15.250 --> 09:16.817
So tell me everything.

09:16.860 --> 09:18.688
I don't know. She seemed
pretty cool, I guess.

09:18.732 --> 09:21.430
What's her deal? Why has she
never been here before?

09:21.473 --> 09:23.824
Okay, her mom and my mom
are like best friends.

09:23.867 --> 09:26.261
And she said the divorce
was like, super-messy.

09:26.304 --> 09:28.524
Apparently, she grew up
in Portland with her dad.

09:28.568 --> 09:30.744
- Guess he died pretty suddenly.
- 'Tragic!'

09:30.787 --> 09:32.484
Let's invite her to the club
tomorrow and get the story.

09:32.528 --> 09:34.791
Why? So she can offend us
all with that flannel?

09:37.925 --> 09:39.840
Shit! Hey, dad.

09:42.756 --> 09:44.453
This your idea of discussion?

09:44.496 --> 09:46.586
Hey! Whatever,
we're all friends here.

09:53.810 --> 09:55.246
Don't look at me.
I didn't touch it.

09:58.554 --> 10:02.384
Ginny, have you heard
from your parents today?

10:02.427 --> 10:05.169
Uh, yeah, right.
They're in Paris. Why?

10:05.213 --> 10:06.997
I got a call
from the dock master.

10:07.041 --> 10:08.738
Your cousin went for a dive
and didn't come back.

10:08.782 --> 10:12.176
Now did she tell you she was
prepping for an overnight?

10:12.220 --> 10:14.788
Kit is fine,
she will show up tomorrow

10:14.831 --> 10:17.442
with some fish skeleton and
like a three-hour explanation

10:17.486 --> 10:19.531
on why it's a prehistoric fossil
or something.

10:19.575 --> 10:22.665
Okay. Just uh, uh,
do me a favor.

10:22.709 --> 10:24.145
Gimme a call when she turns up.

10:24.188 --> 10:25.189
Okay. Sure.

10:26.451 --> 10:27.975
Hey.

10:28.018 --> 10:30.151
Surin Beach?

10:30.194 --> 10:31.195
Let me know
if you hear anything.

10:42.380 --> 10:44.165
You hate it.

10:44.208 --> 10:45.557
No. I-it's good.

10:47.647 --> 10:49.649
You know..

10:49.692 --> 10:53.043
...we should talk about where
you'll go for senior year.

10:53.087 --> 10:55.219
- Do I get a say in that?
- Of course, you do.

10:55.263 --> 10:57.091
It's your future.

10:57.134 --> 10:58.832
Didn't get a choice
about coming here.

11:01.443 --> 11:03.663
Look.

11:03.706 --> 11:05.534
I know how close
you and dad were.

11:05.577 --> 11:09.059
And what a nightmare
this has got to be. But..

11:10.931 --> 11:12.584
It's gonna be
a really long summer

11:12.628 --> 11:14.195
if you're not willing
to give this a chance.

11:15.675 --> 11:16.676
Sorry.

11:18.808 --> 11:21.376
So, what is there to do
around here?

11:21.419 --> 11:22.943
Well, have you
ever been sailing?

11:22.986 --> 11:24.466
We could take
the boat out tomorrow.

11:24.509 --> 11:25.902
Or there's a pool
at the club.

11:25.946 --> 11:28.296
We could order lunch
and go for a swim.

11:28.339 --> 11:30.211
I don't know how.

11:32.430 --> 11:34.215
Greg never taught you?

11:34.258 --> 11:36.870
- Dad couldn't swim, either.
- Oh, of course, he could.

11:36.913 --> 11:38.698
He was a life guard
all through college.

11:40.482 --> 11:41.657
I didn't know that.

11:43.790 --> 11:44.921
[spoon clanks]

11:44.965 --> 11:47.794
[instrumental music]

11:52.102 --> 11:53.930
Is it okay
if I go for a run?

11:56.063 --> 11:59.109
Sure. There's a path
to the dunes.

11:59.153 --> 12:02.373
Uh, make sure you turn around
when you reach the bluffs.

12:02.417 --> 12:03.766
Hey, do you want me
to come with you?

12:07.161 --> 12:08.684
I'm trying too hard.

12:08.728 --> 12:10.294
Aren't I?

12:10.338 --> 12:11.643
A little, yeah.

12:13.558 --> 12:15.256
Just be careful.
Okay?

12:19.913 --> 12:23.786
♪ Street are docks

12:23.830 --> 12:27.007
♪ Frozen there

12:34.101 --> 12:37.452
♪ 'Cause I saw

12:37.495 --> 12:41.978
♪ Stuck in the shallows

12:42.022 --> 12:45.025
♪ I saw

12:45.068 --> 12:49.551
♪ Stuck in the shallows

12:49.594 --> 12:52.815
♪ Saw

12:52.859 --> 12:57.298
♪ Stuck in the shallows

12:57.341 --> 13:00.780
♪ Shallows

13:00.823 --> 13:03.826
♪ All around ♪

13:03.870 --> 13:05.741
[indistinct singing]

13:11.486 --> 13:14.315
[waves crashing]

13:25.848 --> 13:28.633
[eerie whispering]

13:36.903 --> 13:39.819
[instrumental music]

13:42.125 --> 13:44.998
[whispering continues]

13:57.445 --> 14:00.143
[Leo]
'Hey! Hey.'

14:01.884 --> 14:02.972
What are you doing?

14:06.715 --> 14:07.759
I don't know.

14:09.761 --> 14:10.980
You can't swim here.

14:13.113 --> 14:15.332
But surfing
is totally fine?

14:18.814 --> 14:22.165
Right. Well, we're good.
I'm not going back in.

14:23.688 --> 14:27.649
I can't actually swim.

14:27.692 --> 14:29.564
[whispering continues]

14:34.264 --> 14:36.353
That sound.

14:36.397 --> 14:38.094
I've never heard anything
like that before.

14:38.965 --> 14:39.922
You heard that?

14:39.966 --> 14:42.446
Uh, yeah.

14:42.490 --> 14:44.622
I don't know.

14:44.666 --> 14:46.886
Must've come
from one of the boats.

14:46.929 --> 14:47.887
Weird.

14:50.324 --> 14:52.369
I'm Miranda.

14:52.413 --> 14:53.370
Leo.

14:57.113 --> 14:58.810
Whoa. What happened there?

15:01.901 --> 15:02.945
Boating accident.

15:05.513 --> 15:08.342
[eerie music]

15:10.735 --> 15:12.781
You should get going.
Water's coming in.

15:15.001 --> 15:16.524
Yeah. Whoa.

15:16.567 --> 15:19.005
[water gurgling]

15:19.048 --> 15:20.310
It was nice to..

15:22.269 --> 15:25.141
[eerie whispering]

15:34.107 --> 15:36.065
[panting]

15:38.241 --> 15:40.069
[whispering continues]

15:43.464 --> 15:45.248
- Miranda.
- Ha!

15:45.292 --> 15:47.468
- Are you okay?
- What are you doing?

15:47.511 --> 15:49.557
- Were you following me?
- You were gone a long time.

15:49.600 --> 15:51.298
I was worried.

15:51.341 --> 15:52.908
Sorry. I..

15:57.347 --> 15:58.522
I just got spooked.

16:01.873 --> 16:03.092
Are you sure you're okay?

16:03.136 --> 16:04.702
Yeah. I'm fine.

16:07.488 --> 16:10.360
[intense music]

16:25.158 --> 16:26.986
[birds chirping]

16:29.727 --> 16:32.513
[instrumental music]

17:02.630 --> 17:05.502
[music continues]

17:24.042 --> 17:26.871
[engine revving]

17:33.269 --> 17:36.533
You're right.
The new girl's hot.

17:36.577 --> 17:38.796
- Her name is Miranda.
- Miranda?

17:40.407 --> 17:42.104
Well, did you hand Miranda
your balls outright

17:42.148 --> 17:44.063
or did you just
put a sold sign on your junk?

17:44.106 --> 17:46.108
- Shut up.
- Ha-ha.

17:46.152 --> 17:47.283
You know, it just seems
like a lot of work

17:47.327 --> 17:48.763
when Ginny's still dyin'
to climb that that

17:48.806 --> 17:50.547
teach strip pole,
if you know what I'm saying.

17:50.591 --> 17:52.375
Believe it or not,
I can decode

17:52.419 --> 17:53.898
that sort of metaphor.

17:56.597 --> 17:58.425
- Want that?
- Mm.

17:58.468 --> 18:00.601
- Be right back.
- Alright.

18:00.644 --> 18:03.473
[instrumental music]

18:07.956 --> 18:10.785
[indistinct chatter]

18:19.359 --> 18:21.883
Couldn't manage one day
with outside contact?

18:21.926 --> 18:23.537
Yeah.
Something like that.

18:23.580 --> 18:25.930
I get it. Your boyfriend
probably misses you.

18:25.974 --> 18:28.716
Yeah. Javier gets really upset
when I don't check in.

18:28.759 --> 18:31.936
He's a bodybuilder.
So I don't like to make him mad.

18:31.980 --> 18:34.809
Plus, I also
have to email social services

18:34.852 --> 18:37.507
to let them know Amelia hasn't
locked me in the basement.

18:37.551 --> 18:39.640
'Cause that's something
we're worried about.

18:39.683 --> 18:40.771
Probably not.

18:43.122 --> 18:44.123
One second.

18:50.738 --> 18:52.914
Nelson here was actually
just wrapping things up.

18:52.957 --> 18:54.133
Thanks, Nelson.

19:00.487 --> 19:02.750
So, what do you
have to do tomorrow night?

19:02.793 --> 19:05.231
I was thinking
a little brooding

19:05.274 --> 19:07.668
maybe penning some
angsty poetry, for sure

19:07.711 --> 19:09.974
avoiding awkward conversation
with my only living relative.

19:10.018 --> 19:11.759
You know, the usual.

19:11.802 --> 19:13.195
Tried out the whole
poetry thing for a while

19:13.239 --> 19:14.849
after my mom passed away.

19:14.892 --> 19:17.895
My eye in [indistinct]
definitely needs work.

19:17.939 --> 19:20.246
- I'm so sorry.
- Thanks.

19:22.596 --> 19:24.467
Anyway, if you get bored
of poetry, there's this thing

19:24.511 --> 19:26.208
happening down at the yacht club
tomorrow night.

19:26.252 --> 19:28.210
'Sort of an island tradition to
kick off the start of summer.'

19:28.254 --> 19:29.603
You should come.

19:29.646 --> 19:30.995
Good for angst-drowning.

19:33.215 --> 19:35.435
- Yeah. Maybe.
- Alright.

19:35.478 --> 19:36.523
I'll see you there.

19:45.227 --> 19:46.359
[computer beeps]

19:55.846 --> 19:58.501
[indistinct chatter]

20:01.852 --> 20:04.725
[keys clacking]

20:13.516 --> 20:16.345
[instrumental music]

20:24.875 --> 20:27.791
- Oh, my gosh. You're Miranda.
- I'm Cece N. Cooper.

20:27.835 --> 20:29.750
My mom told me not
to bother you this week

20:29.793 --> 20:31.142
because you and your mom
have like tons of bonding

20:31.186 --> 20:32.448
and whatever
to make up for, but

20:32.492 --> 20:33.797
I'm pretty sure
she just said that

20:33.841 --> 20:35.321
'cause her Botox
went a little wanky

20:35.364 --> 20:36.713
and she's desperate
for company.

20:36.757 --> 20:38.193
Anyways, I couldn't wait
to meet you.

20:38.237 --> 20:39.977
Plus Ginny says
you're a total freak.

20:40.021 --> 20:41.675
Which means,
we're gonna be BFFs.

20:41.718 --> 20:44.504
- It's nice to meet you.
- What are you doing right now?

20:44.547 --> 20:45.853
Do you want to grab
ice-cream with me?

20:45.896 --> 20:47.637
My treat, I mean
not that I don't think

20:47.681 --> 20:49.030
you can afford ice cream.
You're..

20:49.073 --> 20:50.249
You don't seem
poor or anything.

20:50.292 --> 20:52.120
I just...wanna be nice.

20:52.163 --> 20:53.730
- I have to be somewhere.
- Okay.

21:00.868 --> 21:04.350
Sorry, uh, you caught me
in weird moment.

21:04.393 --> 21:06.395
- Cece, right?
- Right.

21:06.439 --> 21:08.963
I guess
I'm having a hard time

21:09.006 --> 21:10.747
coping with moving
to a small town

21:10.791 --> 21:12.358
where everyone knows my height,
weight and shoe size.

21:12.401 --> 21:14.142
Oh, no one
can get your shoe size.

21:14.185 --> 21:15.404
I've been trying all day.

21:19.103 --> 21:20.931
[chuckling]

21:20.975 --> 21:22.803
Ginny goes to Deerfield,
but, you know

21:22.846 --> 21:24.674
my parents aren't into
the whole catholic-school thing.

