Scared?

39:02.862 --> 39:04.342
I don't feel anything anymore.

39:06.866 --> 39:09.172
[music continues]

39:09.216 --> 39:10.260
[Cece]
'Hey!'

39:15.265 --> 39:16.702
Be that as it may

39:16.745 --> 39:18.443
as a life guard,
it's my moral obligation

39:18.486 --> 39:20.053
to provide you
with a floatation device.

39:21.881 --> 39:23.622
- Thanks!
- 'Guys, hurry up!'

39:27.321 --> 39:29.367
♪ Oh-oh oh-oh

39:29.410 --> 39:30.933
[laughing]

39:34.241 --> 39:36.112
[indistinct chattering]

39:39.072 --> 39:40.160
♪ Oh-oh oh-oh

39:40.203 --> 39:44.947
♪ Oh-oh oh-oh oh-oh ♪

39:49.343 --> 39:52.172
[indistinct chatter]

39:53.913 --> 39:55.001
[gasps]

39:56.959 --> 39:59.527
Keep laughing, but everyone
is afraid of something.

39:59.571 --> 40:01.486
Not me.

40:01.529 --> 40:03.401
Lemme guess. Spiders?

40:03.444 --> 40:05.011
[chuckles]

40:05.054 --> 40:07.230
- Heights?
- Nope.

40:07.274 --> 40:09.624
Mm, I know.
Hounds.

40:11.060 --> 40:12.453
Failure.

40:15.804 --> 40:16.805
[gasps]

40:18.328 --> 40:20.330
- Not funny!
- That wasn't me.

40:25.118 --> 40:26.380
Let's go back in.

40:34.475 --> 40:35.607
[Miranda screams]

40:38.436 --> 40:39.654
Miranda!

40:41.090 --> 40:43.223
TJ!

40:43.266 --> 40:44.659
Miranda!

40:47.270 --> 40:50.143
[intense music]

41:20.303 --> 41:23.176
[music continues]

41:45.981 --> 41:47.069
[gasps]

41:47.113 --> 41:48.418
[coughs]

41:52.597 --> 41:53.554
[TJ]
'Miranda!'

41:59.125 --> 42:01.475
Miranda!
What happened?

42:03.042 --> 42:05.305
Leo. He saved me.

42:07.612 --> 42:09.265
He was, he was just here.

42:13.661 --> 42:16.534
[instrumental music]

42:24.280 --> 42:27.719
Keep it.
You're still shivering.

42:27.762 --> 42:29.198
Sure you're okay?

42:29.242 --> 42:31.636
Aside from my damaged pride,
all good.

42:31.679 --> 42:33.246
I'm so sorry, Miranda.

42:33.289 --> 42:34.813
Should've never let you go
in the water.

42:34.856 --> 42:37.467
Let me?
TJ, I'm a big girl.

42:37.511 --> 42:39.208
I make my own bad decisions.

42:39.252 --> 42:40.775
You're sure Leo was there?

42:40.819 --> 42:42.342
I mean, no one else saw him.

42:42.385 --> 42:44.779
- Positive.
- I mean, that's weird, right?

42:44.823 --> 42:47.434
The waves and the fogs
just came out of nowhere.

42:47.477 --> 42:49.131
And Leo saves you
and just disappears?

42:50.655 --> 42:52.700
TJ..

42:52.744 --> 42:54.136
Ah, it's nothing.

42:55.268 --> 42:57.357
Just drunk...and stupid.

42:58.488 --> 42:59.751
That make two of us.

43:02.405 --> 43:05.278
[music continues]

43:08.803 --> 43:10.588
Thanks for walking me home.

43:17.507 --> 43:18.465
[exhales sharply]

43:21.120 --> 43:23.992
[water gurgling]

43:41.140 --> 43:43.969
[eerie music]

44:03.162 --> 44:05.077
[gasps]

44:13.215 --> 44:16.044
[instrumental music]

44:35.890 --> 44:37.196
The call's getting stronger.

44:39.415 --> 44:40.460
No.

44:42.157 --> 44:43.463
We need to go
to the caves tonight.

44:43.506 --> 44:45.421
We're almost out of time
to be on land.

44:48.381 --> 44:51.514
You ever hear about
one of the heirs..

44:51.558 --> 44:53.429
...hearin' it?

44:53.473 --> 44:58.304
The call? What kinda question
is that?

44:58.347 --> 44:59.784
[Finley]
'You heard
anything interesting?'

45:03.526 --> 45:04.658
Uh-oh!

45:04.702 --> 45:06.268
I feel a lecture comin'.

45:06.312 --> 45:08.531
They're doin' an autopsy
on Kit Morgan.

45:08.575 --> 45:10.272
They're gonna know
it wasn't a shark.

45:10.316 --> 45:11.883
Who cares?
Let 'em try to figure out

45:11.926 --> 45:13.580
what kind of an animal
does that to a body.

45:13.623 --> 45:16.626
[Leo]
There wasn't supposed
to be a body.

45:16.670 --> 45:18.803
Don't you get it?

45:18.846 --> 45:20.630
They're gonna comb Surin Beach.

45:20.674 --> 45:22.807
And they won't stop until
they find somethin' to blame.

45:22.850 --> 45:25.505
She had a knife.
It's harder than we thought.

45:25.548 --> 45:26.593
You dragged my sister into this?

45:26.636 --> 45:27.768
I wanted to help.

45:27.812 --> 45:29.291
I needed someone with balls

45:29.335 --> 45:31.163
to back me up.

45:31.206 --> 45:33.905
Leo, you know exactly
why that girl had to go.

45:33.948 --> 45:36.516
You just didn't wanna
have to be the one to do it.

45:36.559 --> 45:39.388
So come on, brother,
cheer up.

45:39.432 --> 45:41.651
She's dead.
We should be celebrating.

45:41.695 --> 45:42.957
Right?

45:43.001 --> 45:45.873
[instrumental music]

45:45.917 --> 45:46.961
Right.

45:57.232 --> 46:00.758
- Leo..
- Just deal with the body.

46:00.801 --> 46:01.802
Okay?

46:17.426 --> 46:20.299
[intense music]

46:35.140 --> 46:36.358
[knock on door]

46:43.931 --> 46:45.498
I'm here to I.D.
my cousin's body.

46:45.541 --> 46:47.935
Sheriff Colley said
your mom would be coming.

46:47.979 --> 46:49.807
Yeah, well, this isn't
the kinda thing she does.

46:49.850 --> 46:51.460
This is the kinda thing
she makes me do.

46:51.504 --> 46:53.419
So can we
get it over with, please?

46:53.462 --> 46:55.595
[intense music]

46:56.988 --> 46:58.206
It's this way.

47:19.227 --> 47:21.577
[Dave]
Are you sure you don't wanna
wait for you mom or dad?

47:21.621 --> 47:22.840
It's pretty bad.

47:26.191 --> 47:28.758
[music continues]

47:28.802 --> 47:29.890
[inhales deeply]

47:33.241 --> 47:34.590
That's Kit.

47:38.812 --> 47:41.293
I'm so sorry for your loss.

47:44.209 --> 47:47.038
I just wanted to make sure
she was really dead.

47:47.081 --> 47:49.257
She's entitled to
half of Nana Morgan's estate.

47:54.001 --> 47:57.222
Should I g-get you something?
Water, somethin'?

47:57.265 --> 47:59.093
No. I'm fine.
Do you need anything else?

48:00.747 --> 48:03.619
[music continues]

48:10.322 --> 48:11.627
[retching]

48:13.716 --> 48:15.631
[coughs]

48:28.166 --> 48:30.951
[indistinct chatter]

48:33.736 --> 48:36.609
[music continues]

49:06.813 --> 49:09.685
[music continues]

49:12.079 --> 49:13.907
"Seawalker's kiss?"

49:38.105 --> 49:39.541
[door creaks]

49:41.979 --> 49:43.371
[door opens]

49:44.677 --> 49:47.549
[instrumental music]

49:52.902 --> 49:53.991
Deputy Dave?

50:04.218 --> 50:05.524
Oh, my god!

50:07.830 --> 50:09.963
[gasping]

50:10.007 --> 50:12.879
[smoke alarm blaring]

50:16.883 --> 50:18.189
Help!

50:18.232 --> 50:19.581
Somebody help me!

50:22.062 --> 50:23.063
Help me!

50:23.107 --> 50:24.804
Help!

50:24.847 --> 50:25.805
[coughs]

50:31.289 --> 50:34.031
[instrumental music]

50:34.074 --> 50:35.902
[Ginny]
'Fire! There's a fire!

50:35.945 --> 50:37.208
'Somebody help me!'

50:38.470 --> 50:39.732
'Let me out!'

50:41.560 --> 50:42.735
Ginny?

50:44.171 --> 50:45.433
[Ginny]
'Help me!'

50:50.308 --> 50:52.310
[fire alarm blaring]

50:52.353 --> 50:53.398
Ginny!

50:55.139 --> 50:56.183
Ginny!

50:56.227 --> 50:58.098
Help!

50:58.142 --> 50:59.143
Ginny, are you okay?

50:59.186 --> 51:01.754
Okay, we have to go this way.

51:01.797 --> 51:03.060
[explosion]

51:05.888 --> 51:07.847
[sobbing]

51:07.890 --> 51:10.328
[grunts]

51:10.371 --> 51:11.720
Come on. Go, go, go.

51:14.723 --> 51:16.334
[Ginny]
I'm telling you,
someone was in there.

51:16.377 --> 51:17.857
[female #1]
You're still in shock.

51:17.900 --> 51:19.946
It's been a long week
for you and your family.

51:19.989 --> 51:22.644
I heard something and then
there was smoke and fire

51:22.688 --> 51:23.993
'and all the doors
were locked.'

51:26.344 --> 51:27.823
Nothing on this island
is up to code.

51:27.867 --> 51:29.564
And that building is
a 100 years old.

51:29.608 --> 51:31.740
I'd be surprised
if there wasn't a wiring issue.

51:31.784 --> 51:33.655
[Amelia]
'Miranda!'

51:33.699 --> 51:35.135
- Are you alright?
- I'm fine.

51:35.179 --> 51:36.528
- Are you hurt?
- Amelia, I'm fine.

51:38.312 --> 51:40.358
[exhales]

51:40.401 --> 51:43.317
[instrumental music]

51:45.450 --> 51:47.191
[sobbing]

52:13.478 --> 52:16.437
[music continues]

52:16.481 --> 52:19.353
[eerie whispers]

52:42.246 --> 52:45.162
[instrumental music]

52:50.819 --> 52:51.733
[Amelia]
'Miranda?'

52:52.778 --> 52:54.736
How are you feeling?

52:54.780 --> 52:57.565
The EMT said you might wake up
feeling a little wheezy.

52:57.609 --> 52:59.176
- From the smoke.
- I'm okay.

52:59.219 --> 53:01.961
You know, maybe we should
visit the mainland ER.

53:02.004 --> 53:03.092
We-we could still take
the afternoon ferry--

53:03.136 --> 53:04.572
Seriously, I'm good.

53:08.750 --> 53:09.882
I..

53:13.407 --> 53:16.541
I don't know
if I can ever forgive you

53:16.584 --> 53:17.933
for abandoning me.

53:19.805 --> 53:21.285
But I wanna try.

53:21.328 --> 53:24.026
[music continues]

53:24.070 --> 53:25.202
Thank you.

53:29.162 --> 53:31.512
Is this a seawalker?

53:31.556 --> 53:34.080
Yeah. It's been
in the family for ages.

53:36.082 --> 53:38.258
Can you tell me about them?

53:38.302 --> 53:41.522
Y-you wanna know
about island folklore?

53:41.566 --> 53:43.002
People keep talking
about seawalkers.

53:43.045 --> 53:46.135
I'm...just curious.

53:46.179 --> 53:48.181
Okay, sure.

53:48.225 --> 53:50.444
Uh, what do you wanna know?

53:50.488 --> 53:53.099
I heard they can pass
themselves off as human.

53:53.142 --> 53:55.188
So the legend says.

53:55.232 --> 53:58.147
From what I remember, they can
only stay on land so long

53:58.191 --> 54:00.367
before they have to go back
with the tides.

54:00.411 --> 54:03.196
There's a call to remind them.

54:03.240 --> 54:05.024
Supposedly,
if they ignore it

54:05.067 --> 54:07.156
they run out of air
and it kills them.

54:07.200 --> 54:10.595
Unless they steal the breath
from a human's lungs.

54:10.638 --> 54:13.859
The seawalker's kiss.

54:13.902 --> 54:17.297
Yeah, people call it that
because from a distance..

54:17.341 --> 54:18.603
...it looks romantic.

54:22.346 --> 54:24.478
[Miranda]
What happens to the person
who gets kissed?

54:25.610 --> 54:27.089
They die.

54:27.133 --> 54:28.439
So people say.

54:28.482 --> 54:30.528
But I think you're safe.

54:30.571 --> 54:31.877
It's just a legend.

54:33.270 --> 54:34.358
You want some coffee?

54:37.839 --> 54:40.712
[music continues]

54:44.106 --> 54:46.848
[seagulls squawking]

55:07.565 --> 55:08.522
Hey.

55:15.877 --> 55:16.965
What are you doin' here?

55:17.009 --> 55:18.532
I wanted to thank you

55:18.576 --> 55:20.360
for saving me
the other night.

55:20.404 --> 55:22.319
You ran away so fast,
I didn't get a chance to.

55:22.362 --> 55:24.321
Yeah. No problem.

55:25.757 --> 55:27.280
How did you see me?

55:27.324 --> 55:29.195
The waves were like
ten feet tall.

55:29.238 --> 55:31.240
Just luck...I guess.

55:34.331 --> 55:35.854
I gotta get back to work.

55:35.897 --> 55:37.682
I saw your eyes..

55:37.725 --> 55:38.770
...in the water.

55:41.860 --> 55:43.731
I should hope so.

55:43.775 --> 55:44.689
They're right here
on my face.

55:44.732 --> 55:46.386
They were glowing.

55:46.430 --> 55:49.607
Like, full on,
"X-Men" mutant glowing.

55:51.348 --> 55:53.480
Next time you go swimming,
lay off the tequila.

55:53.524 --> 55:55.439
I wasn't drunk when I saw
your scars on the beach.

55:56.440 --> 55:57.702
Where'd they go?

55:59.443 --> 56:02.533
[instrumental music]

56:02.576 --> 56:04.491
You're welcome
for saving your life.

56:04.535 --> 56:06.363
You need to go.

56:06.406 --> 56:07.451
Fine.

56:09.409 --> 56:10.758
What you doing?

56:10.802 --> 56:11.977
Going back in the water.

56:12.020 --> 56:13.326
You can't swim.

56:13.370 --> 56:14.675
- So teach me.
- No.

56:16.851 --> 56:18.070
Fine.

56:21.726 --> 56:23.162
♪ Crazy 'cause I know

56:23.205 --> 56:28.515
♪ I wanna jump

56:28.559 --> 56:33.955
♪ Crazy 'cause the feeling
keeps me high ♪

56:35.740 --> 56:39.004
♪ Crazy 'cause we all
might die ♪

56:39.047 --> 56:41.746
♪ In a dark sky night love

56:41.789 --> 56:45.750
♪ In a dark sky night

56:45.793 --> 56:50.798
♪ Crazy 'cause I know
that I'm alive ♪♪

56:50.842 --> 56:52.496
Disappointed?

56:52.539 --> 56:54.062
A little, yeah.

56:57.544 --> 56:59.154
What did I see
the other night?

57:04.856 --> 57:07.032
Come on in.
You're shiverin'.

57:14.561 --> 57:16.302
[doorbell rings]

57:25.398 --> 57:27.531
- Miranda?
- No. She isn't here.

57:29.750 --> 57:31.012
I took care
of the police report.

57:31.056 --> 57:33.972
Oh, God! Thank you.

57:35.974 --> 57:37.889
You're a good friend.

57:37.932 --> 57:39.499
Don't pretend
this was an act of kindness.

57:41.719 --> 57:43.024
I hope it was worth it.

57:53.905 --> 57:55.210
Here.

57:55.254 --> 57:56.211
Thanks.

58:03.262 --> 58:06.091
[instrumental music]

58:17.972 --> 58:21.062
- Stop looking.
- I'm not.

58:21.106 --> 58:23.848
So, uh, how come you've never
visited the island before?

58:25.589 --> 58:27.416
My dad..

58:27.460 --> 58:29.593
...kind of had a thing
about water.

58:31.899 --> 58:33.205
I miss him so much.

58:35.860 --> 58:37.426
He just died.

58:37.470 --> 58:40.429
And everyday I wake up..

58:41.866 --> 58:45.565
...and I remember
all over again.

58:45.609 --> 58:46.740
And..

58:50.788 --> 58:51.919
I'm sorry.

58:51.963 --> 58:53.094
Thanks.

59:02.582 --> 59:04.279
Something happened to you
in the water.

59:06.325 --> 59:07.587
To your eyes.

59:10.808 --> 59:13.332
Miranda, let this go.

59:13.375 --> 59:14.463
Please.

59:14.507 --> 59:16.770
I don't know if I can.

59:16.814 --> 59:19.599
[instrumental music]

59:29.391 --> 59:32.307
♪ I'll be thinking about you
from Machu Picchu ♪

59:38.009 --> 59:39.184
Hey.

59:39.227 --> 59:40.489
Could you get me
another punch?

59:42.100 --> 59:44.493
♪ Yeah I bet it

59:44.537 --> 59:47.279
♪ Put it all on the line
what you seek you found ♪

59:47.322 --> 59:49.455
Thank you.

59:49.498 --> 59:53.154
♪ I know you don't see it right
now but you're gonna see light ♪

59:53.198 --> 59:56.636
♪ Through caramel skies won't be
scared of the heights ♪

59:56.680 --> 59:58.420
We don't have to stay.

59:58.464 --> 59:59.900
Go home and watch a movie
or something if you like.

59:59.944 --> 01:00:01.946
- I'm fine.
- Ginny, I mean--

01:00:01.989 --> 01:00:03.643
Look, I didn't narrowly
escape death

01:00:03.687 --> 01:00:05.732
to go home
and watch a movie, okay?

01:00:05.776 --> 01:00:07.386
My bad.

01:00:07.429 --> 01:00:10.868
Hey, no, don't go.
I didn't mean it like that.

01:00:10.911 --> 01:00:13.522
Hey, hey. Pussies
who don't cook can't eat.

01:00:17.701 --> 01:00:19.703
♪ Feels like fate
wants me to fly ♪

01:00:19.746 --> 01:00:21.443
♪ We all got wings
so don't you cry ♪♪

01:00:21.487 --> 01:00:24.446
Hey, where have you been?
You're like two hours late.

01:00:24.490 --> 01:00:25.970
Sorry, something came up.

01:00:26.013 --> 01:00:27.928
Come on!

01:00:27.972 --> 01:00:29.887
I'll be right back.

01:00:29.930 --> 01:00:31.715
Miranda.

01:00:31.758 --> 01:00:33.673
You're on your own
on this one.

01:00:36.110 --> 01:00:37.895
Punch?

01:00:37.938 --> 01:00:39.897
It's like 90 proof,
but Bobby made it

01:00:39.940 --> 01:00:41.942
so there's also like
a 90% possibility

01:00:41.986 --> 01:00:44.336
there's roofies in it.

01:00:44.379 --> 01:00:46.251
I'll take my chances, thanks.

01:00:49.428 --> 01:00:51.343
Thanks for last night.

01:00:51.386 --> 01:00:52.692
Yeah, sure.

01:00:55.129 --> 01:00:56.391
- Bye, honey.
- See ya.

01:00:58.524 --> 01:01:00.744
It doesn't make us friends,
you know...last night.

01:01:00.787 --> 01:01:03.311
Is this about TJ?
Because we're good.

01:01:03.355 --> 01:01:05.966
- I don't do that.
- It doesn't matter.

01:01:06.010 --> 01:01:07.359
You just don't belong here.

01:01:07.402 --> 01:01:08.665
[TJ]
'Ginny.'

01:01:11.406 --> 01:01:13.626
Do you mind giving us a sec?

01:01:13.670 --> 01:01:16.020
Sure.

01:01:16.063 --> 01:01:17.325
What's the matter with you?

01:01:17.369 --> 01:01:18.718
What do mean
what's the matter with me?

01:01:18.762 --> 01:01:21.329
What is your obsession
with that girl?

01:01:21.373 --> 01:01:23.636
Are you seriously buying
her whole "Poor me" act?

01:01:23.680 --> 01:01:26.030
It's not an act.
Miranda's dad just died.

01:01:26.073 --> 01:01:27.727
Did it ever occur to you
I might wanna find a friend

01:01:27.771 --> 01:01:29.207
who actually knows
what that's like?

01:01:31.296 --> 01:01:33.472
Okay, I'm sorry.

01:01:33.515 --> 01:01:35.039
You know what? I'm done, Ginny.

01:01:35.082 --> 01:01:38.651
What? No, you can't
break up with me.

01:01:38.695 --> 01:01:40.348
I can.

01:01:40.392 --> 01:01:43.700
- I should have months ago.
- Look, TJ, uh..

01:01:43.743 --> 01:01:46.790
Sometimes I say things and I can
hear how bitchy they are.

01:01:46.833 --> 01:01:49.227
But I-I just can't stop myself.

01:01:50.707 --> 01:01:52.883
Please don't do this to me.

01:01:52.926 --> 01:01:54.754
I'm so messed up right now.

01:01:54.798 --> 01:01:57.235
Kit was like the one person
in my family who wasn't awful.

01:01:57.278 --> 01:01:58.889
- And now she's gone.
- And I'm sorry.

01:01:58.932 --> 01:02:00.760
About your cousin,
I really am.

01:02:00.804 --> 01:02:02.457
But I can't do this anymore.

01:02:02.501 --> 01:02:05.286
[instrumental music]

01:02:20.301 --> 01:02:21.476
Nay?

01:02:24.131 --> 01:02:26.264
It's her. Isn't it?

01:02:28.266 --> 01:02:29.702
What are you talkin' about?

01:02:29.746 --> 01:02:32.009
Miranda.

01:02:32.052 --> 01:02:34.794
That's why you were asking
so many questions yesterday.

01:02:34.838 --> 01:02:36.970
I saw you with her
on the beach.

01:02:37.014 --> 01:02:38.145
....

01:02:40.147 --> 01:02:42.280
I thought it was dad,
but it was you.

01:02:42.323 --> 01:02:44.021
You've been following me.

01:02:44.064 --> 01:02:46.980
